task.summary: Default task

Configure Maven to build project and make an executable jar package Add two idea configuration, a maven one which call maven packaging, and executable one to launch or debug the app, with maven build as dependency.
Add more or less all needed dependencies (except for graphics) and plays a little bit with Javax validations and Lombok code generator.

Add a window interface, allowing us to define some window controller, able to be launch and to take a state. Add some placeholder class such as State, GUIController, ConsoleController and WindowFactory. Checking if an arguments is passed as parameter, and creating correct window controller from this.
Think I globally conceived the main loop and interaction between window controller and game logic.
Now able to create a player, with a name and origin
Add moving console controller.
Adding inventory and looting.
Can now see player statistics.
Begin the inventory system with equip.
Create JSONObject from State and all subclasses

Delete everything and starting fresh. Add GameController, directly construct from the program argument. Also make main a lot prettier by making my own exception, with a custom to String, and catching it to print usage in this unique case of invalid argument passed.
Use Jackson and successfully deserialize items.json
Create services to access constant contains into JSON files resources. Added corresponding models, in read only.
Make a correct window, with a scrollable text area where we'll be able to put information previously displayed in console.
Make a correct window, with a scrollable text area where we'll be able to put information previously displayed in console.

Making some abstract class to manipulate views. Redo a ViewFactory, based on the ControllerFactory we previously have. Correct all warnings giving by idea, even so some is just a warning suppression because IDE can't know that some will be useful later. However, it still delete some crap.
Little step by little step.
New character creation is now available in GUI mode. We will have to automate controller generation through a factory now, base on the state stage.
Correct behaviour when closing window.
Implement NewCharacterConsoleView

Add a ControllerFactory (where I hope will be the only switch case of the project), which make the game structure globally done since we only have now to add controllers and views to manage each stage.
Create a mission generation controller.
Add FreeModeController, MoveController and StatsController with there associated views if needed.
Add Inventory management, with equip and unequip mode. Also correct or suppress warning given by Intellij.
Began CheckController, verifying if player as win or not and if he has loot an item.

Add a FightController with his associated GUI view. Add player possibility to run. Add enemies list in map generations, making sure there levels isn't greater than the current mission. Uppercased all controller title for more clarity.
Adding all console views (at least all ones that already have a GUI view).
We kind a get our combat simulation.
Enemy can now drop object when winning the battle. Also loading enemies and items list in state, so it's shared accross applications and load once.
